[
  {
    "text": "With the introduction of the revolutionary iPhone X ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=0"
  },
  {
    "text": "and AppleTV 4K, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=3"
  },
  {
    "text": "the video playback experience is taken to a whole new level ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=5"
  },
  {
    "text": "with the addition for support ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=8"
  },
  {
    "text": "for high dynamic range and 4K video.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=9"
  },
  {
    "text": "4K typically refers to frame sizes up to 3840 by 2160, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=14"
  },
  {
    "text": "offering an exceptionally detailed ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=19"
  },
  {
    "text": "and high resolution image when compared to HD.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=21"
  },
  {
    "text": "Wide color is supported across iOS, macOS, and tvOS, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=26"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the media frameworks support up to the rec 2020 color space, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=31"
  },
  {
    "text": "which covers about 75 percent of the visible spectrum.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=34"
  },
  {
    "text": "The addition of support for HEVC ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=39"
  },
  {
    "text": "enables the delivery of higher quality video ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=41"
  },
  {
    "text": "at about a 40 percent lower bit rate compared to H.264. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=43"
  },
  {
    "text": "HDR video must be delivered using HEVC.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=48"
  },
  {
    "text": "There are two HDR formats that we support: ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=54"
  },
  {
    "text": "Dolby Vision and HDR10.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=56"
  },
  {
    "text": "HDR10 utilizes static metadata ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=61"
  },
  {
    "text": "that is applied to the entire program. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=64"
  },
  {
    "text": "This metadata should be in the HEVC configuration box ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=66"
  },
  {
    "text": "and not stored in individual sample data.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=69"
  },
  {
    "text": "For Dolby Vision content, we support Profile 5, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=75"
  },
  {
    "text": "which is single-layer, 10-bit HEVC, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=78"
  },
  {
    "text": "and up to level 7. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=81"
  },
  {
    "text": "For both HDR formats, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=84"
  },
  {
    "text": "the content must be encoded using HEVC. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=86"
  },
  {
    "text": "You should include HDR variants of less than or equal to ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=89"
  },
  {
    "text": "30 frames per second. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=92"
  },
  {
    "text": "And you must always provide SDR variants ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=94"
  },
  {
    "text": "for both your primary media content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=97"
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as your I-frame playlists.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=99"
  },
  {
    "text": "In order to help devices select compatible variants, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=103"
  },
  {
    "text": "we have added a new video range tag ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=107"
  },
  {
    "text": "to the HLS specification. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=109"
  },
  {
    "text": "If you include any HDR variants in your playlist, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=111"
  },
  {
    "text": "you must include this tag. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=114"
  },
  {
    "text": "Declare SDR for any standard dynamic range variants ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=117"
  },
  {
    "text": "and PQ for HDR10 or Dolby Vision variants. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=121"
  },
  {
    "text": "This tag is an advisory to the client ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=125"
  },
  {
    "text": "so that it will not attempt to play streams ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=127"
  },
  {
    "text": "that it cannot support.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=129"
  },
  {
    "text": "In order to support HDCP TYPE-1 content protection, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=134"
  },
  {
    "text": "the new TYPE-1 value has been added to the HDCP level tag. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=137"
  },
  {
    "text": "This value is typically applied to content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=142"
  },
  {
    "text": "with a resolution of greater than 1920 by 1080. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=144"
  },
  {
    "text": "This tag is also advisory in nature ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=148"
  },
  {
    "text": "and prevents the client from attempting to playback content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=150"
  },
  {
    "text": "that can't be supported by the currently attached display. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=153"
  },
  {
    "text": "To finish up, let's take a quick look at a few examples ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=157"
  },
  {
    "text": "of how a playlist differentiates the different types of content ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=160"
  },
  {
    "text": "and how the tags we just discussed are applied. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=163"
  },
  {
    "text": "This is an example of a standard dynamic range HEVC stream ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=167"
  },
  {
    "text": "that does not require HDCP. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=170"
  },
  {
    "text": "This second example describes a 4K HDR stream ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=174"
  },
  {
    "text": "as indicated by the PQ value of the \"VIDEO-RANGE\" tag. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=177"
  },
  {
    "text": "The \"CODECS\" tag describes it as a Dolby Vision stream, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=181"
  },
  {
    "text": "and the \"HDCP-LEVEL\" tag indicates that TYPE-1 ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=185"
  },
  {
    "text": "will be required in order to ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=188"
  },
  {
    "text": "successfully playback the stream. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=189"
  },
  {
    "text": "This 4K HDR10 example only differs from ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=193"
  },
  {
    "text": "the Dolby Vision example by the \"CODECS\" tag. ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=196"
  },
  {
    "text": "The \"VIDEO-RANGE\" and \"HDCP-LEVEL\" tags are the same.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=199"
  },
  {
    "text": "For more information on HTTP live streaming, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=205"
  },
  {
    "text": "please visit devleoper.apple.com/streaming ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=208"
  },
  {
    "text": "for access to the HLS authoring guide, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=211"
  },
  {
    "text": "HTTP live streaming tools including the stream validator, ",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=214"
  },
  {
    "text": "and samples of content that\nyou can test in your own app.",
    "link": "https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/tech-talks-501/?time=218"
  }
]